[2] Washington (Skagit County)
Date: Thu 15 Jun 2017 5:47 PM PDT
Source: KING-TV [edited]
http://www.king5.com/news/northwest-washington-state-hit-with-whooping-cough/449433756


A total of 9 cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, have now been confirmed in Skagit County [Washington] and health investigators are looking at additional possible cases.

At this time, the cases do not appear to be linked to any specific school or other public gathering place.

Public Health is urging you to make sure you're vaccinated against the illness. If you suspect you have whooping cough, contact your health care providers.

